<paragraph id="6D0836D113165C48FF2DFB22CEF0FAAF" blockId="18.[166,1225,1215,1433]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">
Distribution. Widespread but rare European species (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013165C48FC67FB22C981FB6F" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[913,1172,1215,1242]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471" refId="ref19613" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Volume 1. Agromyzinae. Nagykovacsi, Pars Ltd., 1 - 416. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.18655 / Agromyzidae. Vol. 1." type="book" year="2015">Papp &amp; Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313165C48FB5BFB22CC07FB4C" bold="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">
In 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113165C48FF50FB42CC19FB4C" box="[166,268,1247,1273]" name="Ukraine" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FEEBFB42CC82FB4C" box="[285,407,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Chernihiv" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Chernihiv</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FE50FB42CF31FB4C" box="[422,548,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Chernivtsi" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Chernivtsi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FDC2FB42CFE6FB4C" box="[564,755,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Dnipropetrovs'k" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Dnipropetrovsk</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FCF4FB42CE71FB4C" box="[770,868,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Kharkiv</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FC85FB42C90FFB4C" box="[883,1050,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Khmel'nyts'kyy" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Khmelnytskyi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FBDFFB42C977FB4C" box="[1065,1122,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Kyiv" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Kyiv</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FB87FB42C9DDFB4C" box="[1137,1224,1247,1273]" country="Ukraine" name="Poltava" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Poltava</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FF2FFB62CC09FAAC" box="[217,284,1279,1305]" country="Ukraine" name="Sumy" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Sumy</collectingRegion>
Regions (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013165C48FE66FB62CF3BFAAC" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[400,558,1279,1305]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref19116" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2012. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 2. 14 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The first record of Melanagromyza provecta (de Meijere, 1910) for Europe. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 20 (2), 56 - 62 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2012">Guglya, 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013165C48FDCFFB62CF63FAAF" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[569,630,1279,1306]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471" pagination="48 - 56" refId="ref19484" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2017. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 5. Seven new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 25 (1), 48 - 56." type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313165C48FD7FFB62CE2EFAAC" box="[649,827,1279,1305]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313165C48FCBAFB62CEC1FAAC" bold="true" box="[844,980,1279,1305]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">first record</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D113165C48FF2DFA82CC1EFA2C" blockId="18.[166,1225,1215,1433]" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">
Bionomics. Widespread in 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113165C48FDB4FA82CFB0FA8C" box="[578,677,1311,1337]" name="Ukraine" pageId="18" pageNumber="471">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
. This aspects were discussed earlier (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013165C48FB9AFA82CDF6FAEF" author="Guglya, Yu." pageId="18" pageNumber="471" pagination="48 - 56" refId="ref19484" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2017. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 5. Seven new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 25 (1), 48 - 56." type="journal article" year="2017">Guglya, 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Furhter developing larva were found in July and September (see material). So, this species can develop more than one generation (two or even three), in opposite as previously thought.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
